    <p>{`##Delayed Notifications
If you are experiencing delayed notifications on Android 6.0 and newer, it may be due to Doze mode. You can turn off Doze for PagerDuty by going to `}<strong parentName="p">{`Settings`}</strong>{` :fa-arrow-right: `}<strong parentName="p">{`Battery`}</strong>{` :fa-arrow-right: `}<strong parentName="p">{`Battery Optimization`}</strong>{` :fa-arrow-right: `}<strong parentName="p">{`All Apps`}</strong>{` :fa-arrow-right: `}<strong parentName="p">{`PagerDuty`}</strong>{` and selecting `}<strong parentName="p">{`Don’t Optimize`}</strong>{`.`}</p>
    <p>{`##Override System Volume
Some versions* of our Android app offer a feature called Override System Volume. The availability of this feature may differ based on your specific device** and/or other installed apps. It is an experimental feature, and we recommend testing it before using it for production notifications.`}</p>
